<subSubSection id="4AB7D3D1FF9AFFA1FF65FB49FB46FAF1" pageId="11" pageNumber="72" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0212805AFF9AFFA1FF65FB49FB46FAF1" blockId="11.[136,1452,510,1346]" pageId="11" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="30D95C48FF9AFFA1FF65FB49FEFEFB06" bold="true" box="[189,318,1179,1205]" pageId="11" pageNumber="72">Comments</emphasis>
:—In Marambaia, it is found from sea level up to 
<quantity id="C5552DBFFF9AFFA1FCB3FB49FC72FB05" box="[875,946,1179,1206]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.409999999999999" pageId="11" pageNumber="72" unit="m" value="641.0">641 m</quantity>
in Dense Submontane Ombrophilous Forest. The indumentum of the branches and petioles are rufous, densely covered by dendritic and rough-setulose trichomes. 
<taxonomicName id="C5ADFBD9FF9AFFA1FF50FB33FE98FB48" authorityName="Raddi" authorityYear="1829" box="[136,344,1249,1275]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Leandra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="72" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis id="30D95C48FF9AFFA1FF50FB33FE98FB48" box="[136,344,1249,1275]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="72">Leandra variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically closer to 
<taxonomicName id="C5ADFBD9FF9AFFA1FD44FB30FADFFB4F" authority="(Candolle 1828: 162) Cogniaux (1886: 120)" authorityName="Cogniaux" authorityPageNumber="120" authorityYear="1886" baseAuthorityName="Candolle" baseAuthorityPageNumber="162" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[668,1311,1249,1276]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Leandra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="72" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="carassana">
<emphasis id="30D95C48FF9AFFA1FD44FB30FCECFB48" box="[668,812,1250,1275]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="72">L. carassana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="663CFDABFF9AFFA1FCE2FB33FBD8FB4F" author="Candolle, A. P." box="[826,1048,1249,1276]" pageId="11" pageNumber="72" pagination="99 - 202" refId="ref23758" refString="Candolle, A. P. (1828) Melastomaceae. In: Prodromus systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis, vol. 3. Paris, Treuttel et Wurtz, pp. 99 - 202." type="book chapter" year="1828">Candolle 1828: 162</bibRefCitation>
) Cogniaux (1886: 120)
</taxonomicName>
, a sympatric species which is distinguished by bracts and calyx tube and lobes that are longer (
<bibRefCitation id="663CFDABFF9AFFA1FB9EFAD7FAF9FAAC" author="Camargo, E. A. &amp; Souza, C. M. &amp; Caddah, M. K. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[1094,1337,1285,1311]" pageId="11" pageNumber="72" pagination="595 - 631" refId="ref23700" refString="Camargo, E. A., Souza, C. M. F, Caddah, M. K. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2009) O genero Leandra, secoes Carassanae, Chaetodon, Niangae, Oxymeris e Secundiflorae (Melastomataceae) no estado do Parana. Rodriguesia 60: 595 - 631." type="journal article" year="2009">
Camargo 
<emphasis id="30D95C48FF9AFFA1FB61FAD7FB34FAAC" box="[1209,1268,1285,1311]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="72">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="663CFDABFF9AFFA1FA9FFAD7FE87FAF1" author="Souza, M. L. D. R. &amp; Baumgratz, J. F. A." pageId="11" pageNumber="72" pagination="32 - 68" refId="ref27362" refString="Souza, M. L. D. R. &amp; Baumgratz, J. F. A. (2009) Leandra. In: Wanderley, M. G. L., Shepherd, G. J., Melhem, T. S., Giulietti, A. M. &amp; Martins, S. E. (Eds.) Flora Fanerogamica do Estado de Sao Paulo, vol. 6. Instituto de Botanica, FAPESP, Sao Paulo, pp. 32 - 68." type="book chapter" year="2009">Souza &amp; Baumgratz 2009</bibRefCitation>
). Additional illustrations in 
<bibRefCitation id="663CFDABFF9AFFA1FDA6FAFAFCD3FAF1" author="Raddi, G." box="[638,787,1320,1346]" pageId="11" pageNumber="72" pagination="111 - 172" refId="ref26660" refString="Raddi, G. (1829) Melastome Brasiliane. Memoria di Matematica e di Fisica della Societa Italiana del Scienze Residente in Modena, Parte contenente le Memorie di Fisica 20 (3): 111 - 172." type="journal article" year="1829">Raddi (1829)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="663CFDABFF9AFFA1FC91FAFAFB41FAF1" author="Souza, M. L. D. R. &amp; Baumgratz, J. F. A." box="[841,1153,1320,1346]" pageId="11" pageNumber="72" pagination="32 - 68" refId="ref27362" refString="Souza, M. L. D. R. &amp; Baumgratz, J. F. A. (2009) Leandra. In: Wanderley, M. G. L., Shepherd, G. J., Melhem, T. S., Giulietti, A. M. &amp; Martins, S. E. (Eds.) Flora Fanerogamica do Estado de Sao Paulo, vol. 6. Instituto de Botanica, FAPESP, Sao Paulo, pp. 32 - 68." type="book chapter" year="2009">Souza &amp; Baumgratz (2009)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
